block.translation:
East fared Egilafter Olrun,

And Slagfith southto seek for Swan-White;

Völund alonein Ulfdalir lay,

Völund homefrom his hunting came,

From a weary way,the weather-wise bowman;

A brown bear's fleshwould he roast with fire;

Soon the wood so drywas burning well,

(The wind-dried woodthat Völund's was).
